 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ucaioirontoe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CaioIrontoe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Threatening Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/3/02 10:24:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What is *dmg bonus*</span><hr size=1> Na dmg bonus is added to your hits randomly. Magic dmg is different tho. Take for instance this sk poker we got in akheva last night. It was 24/32 magic dmg: 6. In this case the weapon really is 30/32(pretty nice, not to mention it had some really nice stats to)<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uugle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ugle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warmly Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/3/02 10:33:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://ugleduklin.tripod.com/sitebuildercontent/sitebuilderpictures/dscn0011s.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What is *dmg bonus*</span><hr size=1> My understanding is that it's like a Proc (with no message), so for instance, in the example above, if the creature doesn't roll a &quot;save&quot; against that kind of attack, then it could be a 30/32 weapon.  <br>
<br>
My question is, does it become a 30/32 weapon, or is it a 24/32 weapon with +6 to damage?  After all, if you were hitting for say 96 with it as a 24/32 weapon, then you would be hitting for 120 with it as a 30/32 weapon.  Or would you be hitting for 102?  Pretty big difference adding +6 to the damage or increasing the base damage by 6. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uurzah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Urzah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/4/02 4:38:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What is *dmg bonus*</span><hr size=1> From what I understand by reading some of the other boards, it's like hitting with another weapon in the same attack.  So a 12/30 bonus 6 would be like hitting with a 12/30 and adding the damage of a 6/30 in the same attack.<br>
