DLmystic <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/utulluinbardy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TulluinBardy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/4/02 7:51:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.800india.com/computers/tulluin/dolphinboy.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What is *dmg bonus*</span><hr size=1> DLMystic is right. Your primary hand damage bonus is added to every attack with your primary hand. Your minimum attack will be 7, if your damage bonus is 6. Damage bonus is not applied to your offhand, thus you can hit for 1. <p><center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=39706><img src=http://www.800india.com/computers/tulluin/tulluinsig33333.jpg border=0></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uparticleboy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>particleboy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/6/02 6:04:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1059.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What is *dmg bonus*</span><hr size=1> Just to add to what TulluinBardy said, damage bonus is purely a function of level.<br>
<br>
For one handed weapons it *was* (level-25)/3 (rounded down).<br>
<br>
For two handed weapons it *was* (level-25)/2 (rounded down)<br>
<br>
I say &quot;was&quot; because this was the old system up until a year or so ago.  Then Verant realised what serious players had known for awhile: and thats the 2h weapons suck.  I can't remember the exact outcome but I think 2h weapons with a delay over 40 got an extra bonus and/or 2h just generally got a bonus.<br>
<br>
At that stage damage bonus wasn't listed on the weapon stats so its existence had been inferred (for example, I'd notice that my warrior's actual critical damage was the damage bonus higher than the &quot;X has hit for critical damage!&quot; message; I forget the exact text).  I guess now that it is listed explicitly it wouldn't be too hard to figure out what the new formula is though I don't htink I've seen it posted anywhere.<br>
<br>
And yes, the bonus is added to every primary hand attack that doesn't miss.<br>
<br>
Its important to consider the damage bonus when comparing weapons.  In your offhand you want the best ratio (damage divided by delay).  In your primary hand you want the best damage output which is compared using this formula:<br>
<br>
(2*damage+damage bonus)/delay<br>
<br>
Whatever weapon that has the best bonus by that formula will do the most raw melee damage over time (assuming identical weapon skills).  Obviously magic damage and procs will complicate this issue.<br>
<br>
Oh as a small anecdote, it was the damage bonus which made the old moss covered branch (and the other one) so ridiculously powerful (considering how easy they were to get).  At level 60, the old damage bonus was (60-25)/3 or 11.  Given a 4/11 weapon thats (2*4+11)/11 or 1.72.  Compare that to, say, the Ragebringer (at 15/25 that would've been about the best available pre-Velious) is a mere 1.64.<br>
<br>
